Key Takeaways:
 1Ô∏è‚É£ Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA) : scales the number of pod replicas automatically based on CPU or memory usage. Perfect for handling variable traffic without manual intervention.
 2Ô∏è‚É£ Vertical Pod Autoscaler (VPA) : adjusts resources (CPU & memory) of existing pods. Useful for workloads that can tolerate pod restarts and require dynamic resizing.
 3Ô∏è‚É£ KEDA (Kubernetes Event-Driven Autoscaler) : scales pods based on external event sources like message queues, databases, or custom metrics. It can even scale down to 0 when idle, saving resources.
